<H3> <TI>   Attempt To Smuggle Heroin Into Saudi Arabia Foiled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0085C Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 21 Oct 93 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0085C </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: ``Attempt To Smuggle Millions of Rupees Worth </F>
of Heroin Into Saudi Arabia Foiled; Ghani Mohammad, Resident of 
Char Sada Was Arrested; He Had Hidden 1600 Grams of Heroin in 
his Luggage.''] 
  [Text] Islamabad (PPI): Customs agents at the airport 
foiled an attempt on Tuesday to smuggle heroin worth millions of 
rupees into Saudi Arabia. The accused smuggler who is a resident 
of Char Sada intended to fly to Riyadh (Saudi Arabia) by Saudi 
plane SV-724 carrying with him more than a kilogram of heroin. 
The accused is believed to be a member of a notorious gang of 
heroin smugglers and his arrest is expected to uncover many 
sensational facts. Reportedly, Customs superintendent Sayed 
Hussain Shah received a tip that a gang of smugglers was trying 
to smuggle a large quantity of heroin into Saudi Arabia by means 
of Saudi airlines. On receiving this information, Customs agents 
at Peshawar airport began a thorough inspection of the luggage 
of passengers and when [the luggage] of Ghani Mohammad son of 
Gul was searched, he was found to be carrying 1600 grams of 
heroin. The accused was arrested under the Customs Act and 
investigation has started. 

</TEXT>

