<F P=106> [News Report: ``42 Kilogram Hashish Recovered After Firing </F>
Exchange''] 
  [Text] Peshawar (News Reporter) -- In an exchange of 
gunfire between smugglers and the Pakistan Narcotics Control 
Board [PNCB], the latter recovered a huge amount of hashish and 
heroin, which was being smuggled to Punjab. The smugglers 
abandoned their car on the road and fled. The police have 
confiscated the car. According to details, Inspector Riza Khan 
and Wasih Allah led a special team from PNCB Peshawar to watch 
the GT Road. One car, tag number CD 122 AF, passed them, and 
they asked it to stop. The smugglers accelerated instead, 
however. The police gave chase, and there was an exchange of 
fire between the smugglers and narcotics personnel. The 
smugglers left their car in the dark near Hakimabad Naushara and 
fled. The Narcotics Control Board personnel searched the car and 
recovered 37 kilograms of hashish and five kilograms of 
high-grade heroin from hidden compartments. A case against the 
smugglers has been registered in the police station at Peshawar. 

