<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> SWEDEN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Members of Cocaine Trafficking Gang Sentenced in Stockholm </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0123D Stockholm SVENSKA DAGBLADET in Swedish 1 Dec 93 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0123D </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm SVENSKA DAGBLADET </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [TT (Press Wire Service) news item: ``Cocaine Smuggler Got </F>
11 Years''] 
  [Text] Stockholm--Eight members of a gang that has traded 
large amounts of cocaine were sentenced on Tuesday [30 November] 
by the Stockholm City Court. The principal, a 29-year-old Swede, 
was sentenced to 11 years in prison for, among other things, 
aggravated drug crime. The other persons involved got varying 
sentences, from nine years in prison to suspended sentences. The 
network was uncovered in the spring of 1989, when two young men 
were caught at Arlanda airport with 4 kilos of cocaine in their 
baggage. The police were able to determine that the men had 
brought the drugs from Colombia, where a 25-year-old Stockholm 
resident had begun a trade in cocaine with Europe. 

</TEXT>

