<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Orders Creation of Commission To Fight Drug 
Use, Trafficking </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3012053293 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0400 GMT 
30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD3012053293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By order of Eduard Shevardnadze, the State 
Commission for Combating Drug Addiction and Drug Trafficking has 
been created in Georgia. The commission is made up of the heads 
of the power departments and also the health and education 
ministers. 
  According to data supplied by the Georgian Internal Affairs 
Ministry, to date over 60 percent of Georgian young people are 
using drugs. This was a report supplied by the IMAPRESS agency. 

</TEXT>

