<F P=101> UKRAINE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Customs Releases Statistics on Marijuana Seizures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0301132994 Kiev VECHERNIY KYYIV in Ukrainian 24 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> WS0301132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev VECHERNIY KYYIV </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Olena Yehorova under the ``Life Details'' rubric: </F>
``Drug Trafficking Increase?'' -- first paragraph published in 
boldface] 
  [Text] According to the news center of the State Customs 
Committee of Ukraine, between 4 and 10 December alone, customs 
services confiscated over 25 kg of marijuana (not including 
other drugs). Over 11 months of this year, only 28.5 kg of 
marijuana were seized. It seems that the worst prognoses begin 
to be corroborated. 
  During the same week, 518 actions against smugglers and 
violators of customs regulations were brought to court; customs 
officers confiscated foreign currencies worth over 1.5 million 
karbovanetses, precious metals worth 283 million karbovantses, 
and nearly 50 million Russian rubles. 

</TEXT>

