<F P=101> COLOMBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cali Cartel Operation Causes Dispute Between Government 
Minister, Valle Governor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2912160293 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0230 GMT 29 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> PA2912160293 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "CMI Television Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] Government Minister Fabio Villegas angrily 
complained today to Valle Governor Carlos Holguin for describing 
a weekend operation against the Cali Cartel as a failure. The 
governor said that Villegas' complaint was offensive. 
  The controversy between the two ranking officials began as a 
result of a letter that Holguin sent to Police Director General 
Octavio Vargas rejecting the way in which an operation against 
alleged drug traffickers was executed in Cali. 
  Villegas responded to the criticism and said that the 
delivery of suspected drug-trafficking criminals cannot lead to 
a decrease in operations. 
  In addition the minister said that in this type of operation 
one cannot judge about any inconveniences caused, and he added 
that he does not understand the motive of any official who 
criticizes the authorities involved in these operations. 
  In another letter Governor Holguin has said that the 
complaint was offensive and that he rejected any attempt to 
disregard him, because he was not questioning the operation as 
such, rather, the way in which it was executed, a way, Holguin 
said, that only guaranteed the failure of the operation. 

</TEXT>

