<F P=100> CHINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Seize 32 Kg of Heroin in Guangdong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3112050293 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in Chinese 0744 GMT 
27 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> HK3112050293 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, 27 Dec (ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE) -- 
Policemen from the Enping County Public Security Bureau of 
Guangdong Province arrested two drug traffickers and seized 32 
kg of heroin on 22 December. In addition, eight other suspects 
of the same case were also arrested. 
  The two culprits, surnamed Gong and Tang, often carrying 
guns 
with them, have been engaging in drug trafficking from Burma to 
mainland China for a long time. The case was tracked down and 
solved by the Enping County Public Security Bureau, which took 
as a clue the rumor among the drug addicts in the county that 
the "rice" (meaning drugs) there was both cheap and fine. 
  Further investigations are now under way for this case. 

</TEXT>

