<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> THAILAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S., UK, Nigeria Join in Drug Suppression Effort </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801040694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0801040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Thailand has been cooperating with the United 
States, Britain, and Nigeria in suppressing drug trafficking in 
Nigeria leading to seizure of 425 kilograms of heroin. 
  Commissioner of the Narcotics Suppression Bureau attached to 
the Police Department Police Lieutenant General Kowit Phakdiphum 
said many Thai Government officers have jointly worked with 
their counterparts in those countries. They include the 
Narcotics Suppression Bureau, the Central Investigation Bureau, 
the Customs Department, and the Office of the Narcotics Control 
Board working in cooperation with the U.S. Drug Enforcement 
Administration, the British Customs Agency, Nigerian authorities 
in cracking down on international drug smuggling rings. 
  Investigation shows that Nigerian drug traffickers come to 
Thailand to smuggle a container of heroin from a port in 
Thailand to the Nigerian capital of Lagos via Singapore. On 
December 31, 1993, the Nigerian authorities seized the container 
of 259 kilograms of heroin in Lagos. The 166 kilograms of 
heroin seized earlier in Thailand from the accused Nigerian had 
been sent to the Nigerian authorities. In this mission, the 
total of 425 kilograms of heroin was seized from the accused 
Nigerian. There was no Thai involved. 
  The commissioner of the Naroctics Suppression Bureau said 
the 
mission has achieved its aim of breaking down an important drug 
racket. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

