<H3> <TI>   Two Americans, One Barbadian Arrested for Heroin Possession </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0801134294 Hong Kong AFP in English 1330 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0801134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, Jan 8 (AFP)--Two Americans and a Barbados 
national were arrested Saturday on charges of possessing and 
trafficking heroin, police said. 
  The two Americans, identified as Yahya Ali Salim, 41, John 
Charles Hulten, 29, and Daniel Game Mungah, 28, from Barbados, 
were arrested in downtown Bangkok when police stopped a taxi 
they were traveling in. 
  Police said they seized 1.3 kilograms (2.86 pounds) of 
heroin. 
  In Thailand convicted drug traffickers face death penalty, 
but the sentence is usually commuted to a lengthy prison term. 
  About two-thirds of the 1,200 foreigners in Thai jails have 
been jailed for drug offences. 

</TEXT>

