<H3> <TI>   Hanoi Court To Deliberate Opium Smuggling Case </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0501095494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0501095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hanoi Municipality People's Court has so far 
heard 145 corruption and smuggling cases, with a total of 175 
defendants. Many of them formerly held important positions in 
the municipality's party and state system. Two defendants were 
sentenced to life, while nine others received prison terms from 
15 to 20 years. 
  The court will handle five corruption and smuggling cases in 
January 1994, including the case of Duong Van Than, a former 
cadre in the Son La organ of control, who smuggled 36 kg of 
opium. 

</TEXT>

