  [Text] The Azerbaijani Security Ministry press service 
reports that the police have prevented the smuggling of 40 tons 
of aluminum from Azerbaijan in the last three days. After they 
took measures, 2.3 kg of narcotic material was seized at Astara 
border post this morning. The material was found in a secret 
compartment of an Ikarus bus with license plate 02AAQ and 
belonging to Baku Intourist Firm. The bus was going from Baku 
to Syria via Nakhichevan. Drivers Mirzeyev Atabala Eshrefogly, 
Aziziv Azizbala Teymushagly, and Chilinger Murselifrasim 
Misirogly were jailed and an investigation was launched. 
  An attempt to smuggle large amounts of goods through 
Dzhalilabad Rayon was also prevented. Mirzeyev Kabil, a 
resident of Dzhalilabad whose activities gave rise to suspicion, 
was detained while trying to illegally cross the state border. 
Some $15,000 and 1.5 million manats were confiscated from him. 
His efforts to bribe the border guards was in vain. He was 
jailed and an investigation launched. 
  Efforts are underway to ensure our republic's security and 
the inviolability of the state borders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

