<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports on antinarcotics operations in countries 
covered by FBIS London Bureau from 24 December - 4 January. 
Sources are given at the end of each report 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  The Civil Guard seized 500 kg of hashish resin at the port 
of 
Algeciras in southern Spain. It was hidden inside a 
refrigerator truck that had been on a ferry traveling between 
Algeciras and Tangier, Morocco. (Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in 
Spanish 1600 GMT 1 Jan 94) 
<H5>  Iran </H5>
  Seventy tons of narcotics were seized during the current 
calendar year, beginning 21 March, an increase of 5 tons over 
the corresponding period last year. (Tehran IRNA in English 1543 
GMT 1 Jan 94) 
  Approximately 1,000 kg of various types of narcotic drugs 
have been seized from smugglers in eastern Iran in the past two 
weeks. The drugs include morphine, heroin, opium, opium residue, 
and hashish. (Tehran IRNA in English 0930 GMT 28 Dec 93) 
<H5>  Italy </H5>
  The Naples police drug squad seized 13 kg of heroin from an 
organization operating between South America and Naples. (Rome 
RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1057 GMT 31 Dec 93) 
<H5>  Russia </H5>

  Two tons of drugs were confiscated in Chechnya by Interior 
Ministry criminal investigation officers from September to 
December 1993. In addition, 6.4 hectares of narcotics plants 
have been cut and destroyed. (Moscow INTERFAX in English 1528 
GMT 30 Dec 93) 
<H5>  France </H5>
  Two Rwandans are being held for importing 1.3 kg of heroin 
hidden in bottles of shampoo. The drugs, estimated to have a 
resale value of 1,000,000 francs, were placed in a false ceiling 
in their hotel room. The drugs had come from Pakistan via 
central Africa. (Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 
1300 GMT 27 Dec 93) 

</TEXT>

