<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Drug Seizures, Arrests for 6 January </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0601214894 </F>
<F P=103> PY0601214894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on drug seizures and arrests related to drug trafficking 
monitored through 6 January. 
<H5>  Argentina </H5>
  The Drug Addiction and Traffic Division, Ditonar, on 20 
December 1993 seized 4.1 kg of cocaine and arrested a woman at 
the Cabo Vallejo police checkpoint on a bus linking Jujuy and 
the federal capital. Ditonar seized approximately 65 kg of 
cocaine hydrochloride and 150 kg of coca in 1993. (San Miguel de 
Tucuman LA GACETA in Spanish 21 Dec 93 p 20) 
<H5>  Peru </H5>
  Colonel Hector Idiarte Rojas, chief of the San 
Martin-Huanuco 
Front Command, reported that 80 National Police members, 
including 13 officers from San Martin, have been charged with 
being involved in corruption, indiscipline, abuse, and drug 
trafficking. Idiarte said four police officers already have been 
dismissed. (Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 19 Dec 93 p A19) 
  On 18 December 1993, the Peruvian Air Force, FAP, 
intercepted 
a small Colombian plane owned by drug traffickers when it was 
about to take off from a clandestine landing strip with 10 bags 
of drugs. The crew escaped. The incident occurred five miles 
south of the township of Palmapampa in Apurimac Valley. The FAP 
has seized 14 small airplanes owned by drug traffickers so far 
this year. (Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 19 Dec 93 p A19) 
  Peruvian Navy personnel arrested 11 "narcoterrorists" and 
seized 20.4 kg of cocaine paste, 16 gallons of ammonium, 6.5 
gallons of sulfuric acid, one scale, and "terrorist" propaganda 
during an operation in Huipoca township in Ucayali in the past 
few days. (Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 28 Dec 93 p A14) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

