<F P=101> PERU </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Directorate Holding `El Vaticano' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1601020994 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1601020994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Global TV News" Newscast] </F>
  [Text] Drug trafficker Demetrio Chavez Penaherrera, alias 
Vaticano--regarded as the Abimael Guzman of drugs--has been in 
the cells of the General Narcotics Directorate [Dirandro] since 
last night. One of the country's most wanted men, Chavez 
arrived in Lima last night, 15 hours after he was captured and 
deported from Colombia. He was immediately taken to the 
Dirandro cells, where he will remain for 15 days under 
investigation, according to existing laws. 
  It was reported no ad hoc prosecutor has been named to file 
the corresponding charges, although the drug trafficker has 
claimed innocence. Dirandro said Vaticano faces five summons on 
drug-trafficking charges. He will be presented to the media 
once the police investigation concludes. 

</TEXT>

