<H3> <TI>   UNDCP Head Giacomelli To Visit 18-23 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1301130294 Tokyo KYODO in English 1110 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1301130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 13 KYODO -- Giorgio Giacomelli, 
undersecretary general of the United Nations International Drug 
Control Program [UNDCP], will visit Japan from January 18 to 23 
to hold talks with Japanese officials on drug problems, Foreign 
Ministry officials said Thursday [13 January]. 
  Giacomelli, who visited Japan in January 1992, is likely to 
call for further contributions from Japan to fight the drug 
problems, the officials said. 
  He is expected to hold talks with Japanese Foreign Ministry 
officials, authorities on drugs and some Diet members, they said. 
  He is also likely to seek the Japanese public's 
understanding 
on the importance of an international drug control system during 
his six-day stay in Japan, they said. 

</TEXT>

