<H3> <TI>   Giacomelli Urges Tokyo To Contribute More Aid for UN 
Antidrug Efforts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1801142194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1401 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1801142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 18 KYODO -- Giorgio Giacomelli, 
secretary general of the United Nations Drugs Control Plan 
(UNDCP), urged Japan on Tuesday [18 January] to give more 
financial aid to the fight against the global narcotics problem, 
Foreign Ministry officials said. 
  Giacomelli made the request when he visited Foreign Minister 
Tsutomu Hata at the ministry. 
  Hata told the UNDCP chief that Japan will cooperate with the 
U.N. program as far as possible, the officials said. 
  Emphasizing that Japan donated 4.5 million dollars to the 
UNDCP in 1993, Hata said Japan recognizes the drug problem as an 
important global issue, the officials said. 

</TEXT>

