<F P=101> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italians Attempt To Cross Into Romania With 7.44 Kg of Heroin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401142494 Sofia BTA in English 2043 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Today" -- BTA lead] </F>
  [Excerpt] Sofia, January 13 (BTA) -- Italian nationals 
Chiro Francesco Saulo from Cetraro and Francesco Piccone from 
Trino were caught in an attempt to smuggle 7.44 kg of heroin at 
the ferry checkpoint on the border with Romania. The drug was 
hidden in the tank of their Rover Austin, Vasko Vasilev, deputy 
chief officer at the Vidin customs, told BTA. The Italians were 
detained and the car confiscated. This is the seventh drugs 
seizure in Vidin since customs officers seized 40 kilos of 
narcotics in late 1992. So far Vidin officers have seized 150 
kilos of drugs. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

