<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Cocaine Dealers Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1401141994 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 14 Jan 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> AU1401141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Viennese Cocaine Dealer Arrested At </F>
Motorway Service Station"] 
  [Text] Two cocaine dealers were arrested at the Bad 
Fischau (Wiener Neustadt district) service station, located on 
the southbound motorway. Gerhard S. (32) and Oswald L. (32), 
both from Vienna, had offered 120 grams of the drug, worth 
100,000 Austrian schillings, to an undercover investigator. 
  Gerhard S. had bought 400 grams of cocaine in Rio de Janeiro 
for the equivalent of 60,000 schillings and smuggled the drugs 
to Austria. He sold some 70 grams in Vienna and consumed 
another portion of the cocaine himself. Another 148 grams were 
seized during a house search in Vienna's fifth district last 
year, as a result of which Gerhard S. spent three weeks in 
prison. 

</TEXT>

