<F P=102>  94P20208B Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 1 Dec 93 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20208B </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Finnish News Service report: "Nearly Four Years in Prison </F>
for Drug Courier in Lahti"] 
  [Text] The Lahti Municipal Court handed a drug courier a 
prison term of almost four years. The 45-year-old Lahti former 
businessman was arrested in October by Swedish Customs 
authorities, with a quantity of almost 8.5 kg of hashish in his 
possession. A body search of the man after his arrival in 
Finland additionally turned up four kg of amphetamines. 
  The man has kept silent during the court proceedings. In 
addition to being sentenced for two cases of aggravated drug 
smuggling, he was also convicted of four firearms violations. He 
did admit to having four illegal weapons in his possession. 
  The man received a prison term of 46 months. He will have to 
reimburse authorities in the amount of 120,000 markkas. This sum 
will pay for a reward in the amphetamines case and the cost of a 
fancy rental truck he used for transporting the hashish. It will 
also pay the fine for the illegally obtained firearms. 
  Lahti Municipal Court determined the value of a submachine 
gun to be 500 markkas, or the amount that the Armed Forces will 
have to pay for a replacement. 

</TEXT>

