<H3> <TI>   St. Petersburg MVD Arrests 4 Drug Dealers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1801094594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 15 Jan 94 First 
Edition p 16 </F>

<F P=103> PM1801094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Sergy Krayukhin report: "Drugs Business Incurs Losses"] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg -- St. Petersburg City Internal 
Affairs Administration [MVD] personnel in conjunction with 
Moskovskiy and Frunzenskiy Rayon task forces have detained four 
drug dealers doing a brisk trade in a prohibited substance. 
  Thanks to a skilfully planned operation, the underground 
dealers were arrested with incontrovertible evidence--while they 
were trying to sell over 20 kg of poppy haulms [makovaya 
solomka]. 
  A resident of Pskov Oblast, a native of Chechnya, was also 
caught on Kolomenskaya Street. Some 17 kg of plant raw 
materials for the production of drugs were confiscated from this 
drug baron. Criminal proceedings have been instituted. 

</TEXT>

