<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Antinarcotics Operations for 5-10 January </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101041694 </F>
<F P=103> LD1101041694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports on antinarcotics operations in countries 
covered by FBIS London Bureau from 5 to 10 January. Sources are 
given at the end of each report. 
<H5>  Iran </H5>
  Antinarcotics agents of the Qazvin Security Force arrested 
members of a narcotics gang engaged in the production and 
distribution of narcotics. The agents impounded 49 kg of opium. 
(Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in Persian 1230 
GMT 6 Jan 94) 
<H5>  Italy </H5>
  At the end of investigations which began in March, the 
carabinieri of the Frascati group have broken up a gang of drug 
traffickers, arresting 11 people and seizing 15 kg of pure 
cocaine and several thousand ecstasy pills. The organization 
operated between South America, Spain, and Holland, with Rome as 
its terminal. (Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0652 GMT 7 
Jan 94) 
<H5>  Ukraine </H5>
  According to the Ukrainian border guard's press service, 
during 1993 border guard units confiscated 7,209 kg of drugs. 
Over 48 billion karbovanets in of smuggled merchandise was 
confiscated, plus $29,000 and 52 million Russian rubles in cash. 
(Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in English 0100 GMT 5 Jan 94) 

</TEXT>

