<F P=101> BRAZIL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Trafficking Gangs Clash in Rio Shantytowns; At Least 12 
People Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1001151294 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 0900 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1001151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At least 12 people were killed during a war between 
two gangs for the control of drug trafficking at the Acari and 
Jorge Turco shantytowns before daybreak yesterday. Two pregnant 
women and two minors were among the dead. 
  A morning of terror began in Acari. Some 30 traffickers 
headed by (Parazao), armed with machine guns and grenades, 
invaded the Acari shantytown and assassinated four individuals 
at point blank range. 
  (Parazao's) men then moved to the Jorge Turco shantytown, in 
Rocha Miranda. Eight more were killed during the ensuing clash. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

