<F P=101> COLOMBIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Captured Peruvian Drug Trafficker `El Vaticano' Deported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1401184594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1200 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1401184594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- General Jairo Rodriguez, 
deputy director of the judicial and general investigations 
police, has disclosed that Peruvian drug trafficking boss 
Demetrio Limoniel Chavez Penaherrera, alias El Vaticano, 
captured in Colombia and deported to Lima last night, had 
entered this country clandestinely through the Amazon jungle. 
  Rodriguez said Chavez Penaherrera had been hiding in Cali 
for 
a year. He added that the Peruvian drug trafficker did not 
resist arrest. He had no documents and offered the Colombian 
policemen $1 million to let him go. 
  According to Peruvian authorities, Chavez Penaherrera is 
wanted for crimes against the public faith [fe], falsification 
of airplane licenses and flags to the detriment of the Peruvian 
state, crimes against public health, and narcotics trafficking, 
specifically shipping approximately 60,000 kg of cocaine paste 
from Peru to Colombia. 

</TEXT>

