<H3> <TI>   Italian Mafia Member Arrested, Awaiting Deportation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2101201494 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2101201494 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] (Guido Lucatto), allegedly a member of the 
Italian Mafia, was arrested in Santa Cruz and has been 
transferred to La Paz. While he faces no narcotrafficking 
charges in Bolivia, there are grounds to deport him because he 
carries a forged passport. 
  Here is a report by Amalia Pando: 
  A capo of the Italian Mafia was arrested on 17 January in 
Santa Cruz. He will be deported without any judicial 
proceedings within a few hours or days. Four Italian policemen 
arrived in Bolivia yesterday to take him away. 
  He arrived in Bolivia in August 1992 carrying an Italian 
passport issued to the name of (Guido Lucatto) but it has been 
established that the passport is forged. His real name is 
(Salvatore Sciula). He was born in Palermo on 21 February 1950. 
He is 44 years old. He is married to Chilean citizen (Claudia 
Guzman Onoratto). He was arrested by the Santa Cruz Special 
Force with the cooperation of the Italian Police and Interpol. 
  (Salvatore Sciula) was arrested at 0900 on 17 January. He 
and an unidentified man tried to flee when they realized they 
were being followed while crossing a downtown street aboard a 
black jeep. (Sciula) was arrested but his companion is still at 
large. Right now fingerprint tests are being conducted to verify 
that this is the man being sought by the Italian Police. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

