<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> BOLIVIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coca Growers' Leader Says Government Not Fulfilling Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2101194094 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2101194094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nestor Bravo, the leader of the five coca growers' 
federations in Chapare, has said that the government is not 
fulfilling the agreement signed at the end of 1993 during the 
Chapare coca growers' march on La Paz. 
  Bravo stated that the government should have issued a 
written 
response to the peasants' demands to revise Law 1008, 
industrialize coca, and participate in the planning of 
alternative development programs. 

</TEXT>

