<H3> <TI>   Pepes Sends Letter to Escobar's Mother </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2401155394 Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO in Spanish 20 
Jan 94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> PA2401155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota EL NUEVO SIGLO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The self-styled group Persecuted by Pablo Escobar 
(Pepes) yesterday announced that it will remain alert to the 
appearance of "new Machiavellian individuals." 
  The clandestine group made the announcement in a letter to 
Hermilda Gaviria de Escobar, mother of the late drug trafficker 
Pablo Escobar, in which it reported that, contrary to the 
intentions of the Escobar family to sign a peace agreement, 
remnants of the Medellin Cartel are not thinking of peace. 
  "You and the criminal organization of your late son know of 
our capacity. Our objective is to stop the appearance of new 
Machiavellian individuals like Pablo Escobar," the Pepes noted. 
It added that "your intention is not shared by the remaining 
Medellin Cartel members. This is an aspect that worries us 
because it would turn us into victims, a situation that we will 
not accept under any circumstances." 

</TEXT>

