<F P=101> IRAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antinarcotics Measures Include Closure of Eastern Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2001205894 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2001205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The headquarters for a campaign against narcotics, 
in a session today chaired by Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani, approved 
in general terms a draft memorandum of understanding for 
regional cooperation by Iran, Pakistan and Afghanistan. It 
provides for a more determined campaign against narcotics under 
UN supervision. 
  At the session, the president expressed satisfaction and 
appreciation over efforts undertaken by those engaged in 
anti-narcotic operations in the country. He stressed the need 
for political and infrastructural measures including the closure 
of the eastern borders of the country, identification and 
destruction of internal narcotics production and distribution 
networks, and creation of employment and rehabilitation camps 
for addicts. 
  The commander of the law enforcement forces and the 
secretary 
to the headquarters for anti-narcotic operations announced at 
the session that during the current year [beginning 21 March 
1993] 66 tonnes of various types of narcotics have been 
uncovered and more than 53,000 production and distribution 
agents and narcotic addicts have been arrested. 
  According to a report by our correspondent, during the 
session a proposal by the governor general of Sistan va 
Baluchestan Province concerning a plan for closing the eastern 
borders was raised and the required funds for the project 
approved. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

