<H3> <TI>   Drug Act Amended To Allow Confiscation of Drug Smugglers' 
Property </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0140A Lahore MUSAWAT in Urdu 25 Nov 93 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0140A </F>
<F P=104>  Lahore MUSAWAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "Decision To Confiscate Drug Smugglers Property"] </F>
  [Text] Formal permission to amend Article 35(C) of the Drug 
Act has been given in a meeting chaired by Prime Minister 
Benazir Bhutto. This amendment will allow the courts to 
confiscate all land and property of drug smugglers who are 
sentenced to more than two years in jail. The Pakistan People's 
Party government has started to take action to rid the society 
of the cures of narcotics, and has decided to amend the law in 
order to confiscate property belonging to drug smugglers. This 
is a very good step, however, the big fish manage to avoid being 
caught in the present system. They free themselves with the help 
of the police. The ordinary peddlers and the dealers are 
arrested. The system should be overhauled so that the real 
criminals are caught and given exemplary punishment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

