<H3> <TI>   Tribal Authorities Demolish Homes of Drug Smugglers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0135B Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 26 Nov 93 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0135B </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Homes of Three Drug Smugglers Demolished"] </F>
  [Text] Mir Insha (Special correspondent) -- Homes belonging 
to three drug smugglers in Ditta Khel village in Mir Insha area 
were blown up using dynamite. The action was taken on the 
instruction of Mohammed Amin Khatak, the political agent there. 
A.P.A. Shafir Allah, commander of Tochi Scouts; Major Liaqat 
Ali, tehsildar; Mir Inshah Ghazi Mirjan; and Subedar Taj 
Mohammed also took part in this operation. This action was part 
of the clean up operation aimed at the antisocial elements. The 
tribal representatives in the region have expressed satisfaction 
at this action. 

</TEXT>

