<H3> <TI>   Heroin Den in Abbotabad Raided </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0140E Peshawar MASHRIQ in Urdu 9 Dec 93 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0140E </F>
<F P=104>  Peshawar MASHRIQ </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Abbotabad Heroin Den Raided"] </F>
  [Text] Abbotabad (News Bureau) -- The police very 
efficiently raided an old heroin den located in a densely 
populated part of Abbotabad and arrested a person after 
recovering 40 kilograms of hashish and a huge amount of heroin. 
According to the information available, a meeting was held under 
the chairmanship of Tanvirul Haq, SSP [Senior Superintendent of 
Police] of Abbotabad who is very interested in eradicating the 
curse of narcotics, to discuss effective strategies to clean up 
the traders of death in the area who were involved in narcotics. 
Roural Abbas Hussein, ASP [Additional Superintendent of Police] 
of the district, requested cooperation of the residents of Basti 
Jhuggian. The Cantonment police established a check point on 
Murree Road and a Suzuki with license plate number APA-1544 
tried to speed through the check point. Mohammed Ilias, SHO 
[Station House Officer] of Cantonment, chased and then searched 
the Suzuki. He found 42 kilograms of hashish and arrested the 
driver, Mubarak Khan. The Cantonment police also raided a place 
in Sheikh Albandi and recovered a huge amount of narcotics, and 
arrested the leader of the smugglers. 

</TEXT>

