<H3> <TI>   Gender Cited as Reason for Granting Female Drug Smuggler Bail </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WD0135C Lahore NAWA-I-WAQT in Urdu 7 Dec 93 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0135C </F>
<F P=104>  Lahore NAWA-I-WAQT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [News Report: "Female Drug Smuggler Released on Bail"] </F>
  [Text] Islamabad (Special correspondent) -- A female 
arrested for trying to smuggle heroin abroad was released on 
bail. The full Bench of the Supreme Court accepted the accused's 
bail plea. The Bench was composed of acting Chief Justice 
Shafiul Rehman, Justice Abdulqadir Chowdhery, and Justice Ghani 
Mohammed. The suspect Asima was accused of trying to smuggle two 
kilograms of heroin in London and was arrested at Heathrow 
airport. She was returned to Pakistan and the Pakistan Narcotics 
Control Board had taken her into custody. The accused was sent 
to jail where she later spent 10 months and 18 days. Her appeal 
for bail was refused by various courts before it. However, the 
Supreme Court because of her gender has released her on a bail 
of 100,000 rupees. Two other persons, Matlub Hussein and Ziaul 
Din, were also arrested when Asima had fingered them. They have 
been jailed. Ilias Siddiqi represented Asima in the bail 
proceedings and Attorney General Mumtaz Ali argued on behalf of 
the government. 

</TEXT>

