<H3> <TI>   Dane Convicted of Smuggling 3.7 Kg of Hashish </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20251B Reykjavik NEWS FROM ICELAND in English Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20251B </F>
<F P=104>  Reykjavik NEWS FROM ICELAND </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Quick Sentence Meted Out to Young </F>
Drug Smuggler"] 
  [Text] A 24-year-old Danish male has been sentenced to 
eight months in prison a mere two weeks after being nabbed in 
Reykjavik with 3.7 kilograms of hashish. 
  The man initially claimed he had been contracted to funnel 
the illegal narcotic to Iceland on the basis of an 
acquaintanceship struck up in Amsterdam, and in return for a 
$2,500 fee. 
  The illegal stash was then to be picked up in Reykjavik 
after 
he had checked into a hotel. 
  During court questioning the Dane related that he feared 
retaliation from his "employer," of whose identity he had no 
idea other than that he went under the name of Franck, and was a 
foreign citizen residing in Iceland. 
  Despite making pronouncements to the contrary, the Dane 
subsequently claimed he had acted alone in smuggling the hashish 
into the country. 

</TEXT>

