<F P=101> GEORGIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Massive Operation' Against Drug Dealers Underway </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2401230394 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
24 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2401230394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] According to experts, in the last two years there 
has been a significant increase in the availability of drugs in 
Georgia, mainly from Azerbaijan and the Tskhinval region. 
  On 22 January, Georgian law enforcement bodies started a 
massive operation against drug dealers in Georgia. The republic 
was divided into nine sectors. In each the operation was headed 
by deputy security and internal affairs ministers. It involved 
1,500 people. As a result of the operation, 20 machine guns and 
carbines and about 50 kilos of drugs were confiscated, and 12 
stolen cars were recovered by 24 January. About 20 people were 
arrested. According to the spokesman of the Internal Affairs 
Ministry, some high ranking officials have been implicated in 
drug trafficking. 

</TEXT>

